body_html:
Apologies if this does not helpful but I have an idea. I am pretty new but I used Slim recently and while there are a number of warnings, I think your issues is here:

predictions = vgg.vgg_16(images, is_training=True)

should be something like

logits, end_points = vgg.vgg_16(images, is_training=True)

or

predictions, end_points = vgg.vgg_16(images, is_training=True)

If you prefer predictions as the name.

The documents might be poor in areas, especially contrib, but I find even though I do not understand Python that if I follow the stack trace I often solve most problems even if the documents are not complete. I hope this helps and good luck in the future. I am closing the issue because I am pretty confident this will fix your problem, but feel free to reopen if my guess was wrong.

See source code for where the functions returns a tuple not one value.

body:
Apologies if this does not helpful but I have an idea.  I am pretty new but I used Slim recently and while there are a number of warnings, I think your issues is here:

`predictions = vgg.vgg_16(images, is_training=True)`

should be something like

`logits, end_points = vgg.vgg_16(images, is_training=True)`

or

`predictions, end_points = vgg.vgg_16(images, is_training=True)`

If you prefer predictions as the name.  

The documents might be poor in areas, especially contrib, but I find even though I do not understand Python that if I follow the stack trace I often solve most problems even if the documents are not complete.  I hope this helps and good luck in the future.  I am closing the issue because I am pretty confident this will fix your problem, but feel free to reopen if my guess was wrong.  

See [source code](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/433e706bfe0145845911bce0d26e44c9a821b4d4/tensorflow/contrib/slim/python/slim/nets/vgg.py#L198) for where the functions returns a tuple not one value.
